Breathtakingly gorgeous antique Art Deco mirror with rose-pink tinted glass!
Y'all - I am in love with this mirror. I feel like it should be in the Great Gatsby because it's so quintessentially Art Deco! Two toned Art Deco mirrors can be very rare and hard to come by. Not to mention rose colored glass is such a novelty.
The mirror consists of four beveled glass panels alternating between regular and pink tinted glass. The mirror is held in place to its solid wooden back with 6 metal clips and is hung on the wall with its beautiful original metal chain. The tinted glass is a lovely rose pink that creates warmth and a stunning reflection on the wall! The bevels on the glass go around all sides of each panel and capture the light beautifully. 
Condition: The far left of the top pink panel has a tiny spot where a piece of glass cracked and came loose. It was wedged into place to where it was not falling out, but I glued it down just to make sure. There are a couple of small areas where some age spots or "silvering" is occurring under the glass, but they only add to its character in my opinion! The mirror is in overall wonderful condition and the shape and color are so unique! 
Measurements: 15" tall, 18" wide, 3/4" thick, 16" total length chain

Product name: Silver Bracelet, Whiting & Davis, Wide Clamper, Repousse Metal, Floral Design, Silver Bangle, Vintage 1950s
Description:
ITEM DETAILS
Approx. Size:   Inner diameter: 2.5"; Width: 1.25" (6 x 3 cm)
Condition:  Very good.  Very minor finish loss commensurate with age.  See final photo Bracelet has a very nice patina.
Mark/Label:  Whiting & Davis Co Mesh Bags
Vintage Item - Only One Available – Buy Now!
Whiting & Davis silver metal bracelet with raised repousse floral pattern.  This bracelet is a real impact piece.  Wide clamper bracelet.  Ornate baroque design with small faux pearls inside the blossoms.  #JB111
In the repousse process the bracelet is hammered from the inside to create the pattern. The overlayed pieces are hammered separately and then soldered to the repousse base. This process is what gives this bracelet such a dimensional and impactful design.
Whiting & Davis originally opened as the Wade, Davis & Co in 1876.  In 1880 Charles Whiting joined the company and worked is way up the company from errand boy to artisan to the New York sales rep in ten years.  In 1892, Charles Whiting wove by hand the first Whiting & Davis handbag from gold metal mesh, creating one of the first “It” handbags.   The company also created their second iconic design, the snake bracelet late in the 1890s. By 1896, Charles Whiting had partnered with company cofounder Edward Davis and the name Whiting & Davis was born. Throughout the 20th century Whiting & Davis created highly sought after metal mesh handbags, jewelry and other accessories.  The company is still in existence today using modern jewelry marks to differentiate new items from vintage pieces.

Product name: 100% Pure Virgin Neem Oil (organic, undiluted, unrefined)
Description:
100% Pure Virgin Neem Oil (organic, undiluted, unrefined)
About 75% of Ayurvedic remedies contain some form of neem! Indians call the sacred neem tree "the village pharmacy", and have limitless faith in its abilities.
Neem oil is pressed out of the seeds obtained from neem trees. In addition to its use as an organic insecticide spray, it has been used medicinally and in the cosmetics industry. 
Neem oil is used on humans, on animals, and on plants, for a huge range of different problems.
How to use 100% pure cold-pressed Neem Oil:
Recommended ratio for making spray solution: mix 1 teaspoon pure neem oil in a quart of warm water and 1/4 tsp. castile soap. Shake it  well to mix properly. Quantity of neem oil can be increased proportionately for making spray in larger quantities.
Here is some ways to use Neem oil below. Remember: to keep your dilution of Neem oil to about 2 - 5% of any mixture that you apply directly onto your skin.  Some of the recipes below use higher percentages - but keep a lookout for any skin irritation.
Cuts, wounds, minor skin disorders and mosquito and insect repellant
Mix with a carrier oil in a ratio of 1:5 and apply to affected area.
Athlete’s foot
Add 15 ml to warm water and soak the feet in this preparation.
Head lice
Mix 50/50 with a carrier oil and massage into the hair and scalp. Leave on for 1 hour and shampoo. Repeat once weekly for 3 weeks or as long as the problem persists.
Stop mosquitoes breeding
Spray or pour oil on all breeding areas. The oil can be emulsified (to mix with water) by adding Castile or any natural liquid soap.
Plant protection
Add 30 ml to 1 liter of water and add 1 ml of castile or any natural soap. Mix well and spray immediately for plant protection. Do not store the mixture; make fresh formulation for each spray. Spray the mixture on top of all the leaves and on the undersides where insects often hide – you can also spray it around the roots.
Lamp oil to ward off mosquitoes
Add 5 – 10% oil to any lamp oil and burn lamp normally.
Dandruff and itchy scalp
Add a few drops to your regular shampoo.
Ticks and fleas on animals
Add a few drops to your normal pet shampoo (ratio should be 30 ml (1 oz.) to 240 ml (8 oz.) shampoo). Personally we have found that plain castile soap works the best.
Warts
Apply 1 drop of undiluted oil directly on warts once per day. Watch carefully for any possible irritation, and should that occur discontinue use. Continue for 2-3 weeks.
Psoriasis, cold sores, eczema, athletes foot, skin ulcers and other fungal skin conditions
Mix 1 tablespoon (15 ml) with 4 ounces (120 ml) carrier oil such as jojoba or grape seed oil and apply twice a day to affected skin. Should skin irritation occur, discontinue use, or make mixture with less Neem oil.
Pet and livestock spray for ticks, fleas, mange mites and other pests
Mix 1 ounce (30 ml) oil with 1 gallon (3.8 liter) water and add a few drops of Castile Soap (to emulsify the oil). Place mixture into a spray bottle or other type of sprayer, and spray animals once every two weeks. (This mixture can be used on indoor and outdoor plants as well as flowers and vegetables.)
Cleaning the house
Add to carpet shampoos and spray mattresses to kill dust mites.
Hand wash
Add a couple of drops to liquid hand soap for antibacterial properties.
FOR ALL THE ABOVE
As Neem oil has a rather strong smell you might want to add a few drops of essential oil to any mixture to mask the smell. Lavender or lemongrass essential oils work well – but you could add your personal favorite.
 
Store neem oil in a cool dark place, away from sunlight. In case neem oil solidifies due to low temperatures, put the bottle in warm water (below 95 degree F) to liquefy. Putting the bottle in very hot water may reduce the effectiveness of oil.
Botanical Name: 100% Pure, Unrefined  Azadirachta Indica. Neem Oil.
 
Country of Origin- India
Cultivation- Wild Grown
Extraction Method- Cold Press/Unrefined
Texture- Semi-Solid
Color- Yellowish brown to dark greenish brown liquid. 
Scent- Neem Carrier Oil has a pungent, earthy, green musty smell. Some people say it smells of garlic, other think it has an onion  smell.
Shelf Life- 1-2 years 
More information about Neem Oil you can find at:
http://www.neemfoundation.org/

Product name: Shark Toy Soap- Soap with Toys- Guest Soap- Party Favors
Description:
Shark Toy Soap- Soap with Toys- Guest Soap- Party Favors 
Shaaaaark!!! Let your little one's imagination run wild with these fun soaps! You can even use them for themed party favors or guest soaps! These glycerin based soaps contain a little shark toy "swimming" inside. Each bar is hand poured and weighs approximately 3 - 3.5 oz. each and measures 3 x 2 x 1.  inches. I will choose at random the toys that you get so it will be a surprise! Choose the desired quantity from the drop down. If you would like a scent, message me, otherwise they will ship unscented. Soap will ship wrapped in clear plastic wrap to avoid exposure to moisture.
WARNING: CHOKE HAZARD
Adult supervision is highly recommended as every soap contains a small toy that could find it's way into your little ones mouth. Also note, that the toy is made of plastic and could scratch if used on bare skin. I recommend rubbing the soap on a loofah or washcloth to bathe. If you choose scented soap, while it may smell delicious, it is not edible. 
GLYCERIN DEW
Glycerin moisturizes by drawing water into itself. The theory is that when you wash with glycerin soap, there will be a thin layer of glycerin left behind, which will then draw moisture from the air, onto your skin (thus, moisturizing your skin). When the soap sits out, the glycerin in the soap may draw the moisture out of the air, and onto the soap. If you live in a humid environment, you may find that your soap has water droplets on it or get ‘glycerin dew.’ Try to keep your soap in a cool, dry environment. DO NOT LEAVE IT IN SUNLIGHT. Please also note that if you choose a scent, it may discolor the soap over time. 
Ingredients:
Soap Base- Organic Coconut Oil, Organic Palm Oil, Glycerin (kosher, of vegetable origin), Purified Water, Sodium Hydroxide (saponifying agent), Sorbitol (moisturizer), Sorbitan oleate (emulsifier), Soy bean protein (conditioner)

Product name: 100% Pure Hemp Seed Oil (organic, cold pressed, unrefined)
Description:
Hemp seed oil is a great non-clogging oil that helps to reduce the size of pores, blackheads, acne, protects the skin from free radicals and provides the body with essential nutrients required in order to maintain epidermal lipids, skin’s water barrier, elasticity and softness. In addition, it has anti-inflammatory benefits, reduces redness and is recommended for the treatment of psoriasis and eczema.
Hemp seed oil contain a beneficial amount of amino acids, and vitamin E as well. It is a natural antioxidant, and the oil doesn't stick to your skin as many oils have a tendency to do. It is rich in not only Omega-3 and Omega-6, but also Omega-9 - this will allow hemp seed oil to moisturize your skin and keep it healthy - and it does this without clogging your pores.
Potassium and calcium are also found in hemp seed oil products, making it even healthier for your skin.
Hemp seed oil contains ingredients that gives it unique anti-inflammatory properties that are not often found in other oils. This, added to its antioxidant properties, allows hemp oil to detoxify and clean your skin, as well as evening out your skin tone. Hemp Seed Oil is high in Omega fatty acids and proteins. It is a fantastic cosmetic grade oil due to its nutrients.
GENERAL INFO:
Botanical Name- 100% Cannabis sativa
Country of Origin- Canada
 
Extraction Method- Cold Pressed
Processing Type: Unrefined 
Texture- Liquid
Color- Dark brown-green.
Absorption- Hemp Seed Oil is easily absorbed in to the skin. 
Scent- Being unrefined, Hempseed Oil has been left in its virgin state after pressing. It has smell of freshly cut grass. This oil has not been run through filters or chemical processes, so stronger colors and fragrances should be expected. This is completely natural. 
Shelf Life- 1-2 years

Eternalise the past by scanning in old photos or handwritten love notes, include documents of your favourite recipes or stories, remember those funny text messages with phone screenshots and edits, add links to your in-joke websites or the ones that really meant something to you both… Possibilities are endless!

Product name: Best Cribbage Board, 3 player Premium  Cribbage Board, 16.5"L  x  6"W  x  2"H, Two Tier, Maple Top/Cherry Bottom, Laser Engraved, Paul Szewc
Description:
This fun wooden cribbage board can be played with 2 players, 3 players or 4 players (partners).
The board was designed and made from solid hardwoods by Wood Artist Paul Szewc of Guelph. The top is made from solid Hard Sugar Maple and the bottom is solid North American Black Cherry.
Frustrated with the standard cribbage board, Paul took a new direction on the cribbage board. He has drilled the peg holes further apart so you can grip the pegs easier.  As Paul grows older his eyes don’t see as well as they used to, so he has enlarged the numbers for easier reading. The scoreboard has been laser engraved—an upgrade from the screen-printed boards normally seen. The laser engraving will not wear off.
The "wonky" design of the board and the custom laser-engraved skunk and double skunk images add his own flare. The wonky design is like his mini wonky jewelry boxes - whimsical.
It is finished with multiple sandings and sprayed with sealer then sanded again and then sealed. This creates that smooth-to-touch finish. This process is the same as what a high quality piece of furniture receives. It is very durable and requires no care.  Simply wipe with a damp cloth if it becomes dirty. It will last for many years to come.
Each unit comes with a product gift tag and scoring pegs. Please see below for scoring peg options. View the first photo which shows wooden pegs and the other photos which show the metal pegs; pick which one you would like. Playing cards are NOT included. 
Scoring Peg Options:
Wooden - Red, Black, Natural
Metal - Gold, Silver, Black
 
The top fits snugly into the base, held in place by rare earth magnets. The bottom compartment is the perfect place to store a deck of cards and scoring pegs. A great way to keep everything together and transports well. 
This 3 player cribbage board is a delight to use and a delight to the eye!
Total dimensions of nestled unit  are 16.5"L  x  6"W  x  2"H.  
Due to variance in wood grain, your item may differ slightly from the one pictured.
NOTE: HOW TO ORDER
To order a board with wooden pegs only pick Wood/no personalize
                               with metal pegs only pick Metal/no personalize

If it doesn't fit there we put in on the back of the lid. If you wish it to be elsewhere you need to specify in Note to Shop.) Personalizing a board DOES NOT SLOW shipping response time. Product name: Vintage Lace Borders - white lace digital borders, ivory lace borders, photography overlay, wedding clipart, printable Instant Download 5017
Description:
Lace digital borders are made from real vintage lace patterns. These 8 unique designs are organic and imperfect, just like real lace! See closeup photos for details.
There are 8 different designs, and each comes in white, ivory, and a 50% transparent black shadow version. The shadow can be layered with the other colors if you need to make the lace stand out against lighter backgrounds. 
They're each at least 12 inches long, and the ends match up, so the patterns can be repeated to be even longer if needed.
About white digital files: on most home & copy center printers, white in your design will print as clear, not white. A white image printed on colored paper will just display the paper. To appear white, a white image needs to be printed on white paper, and needs to be placed on some kind of background or surrounding color in the digital file. (To print in actual white ink you'd need either a high-end machine or a professional printing press.) Similarly, any light-colored images will not print well on darker paper - the paper will show through the ink. Please keep this in mind when considering the paper you use, and how to create your design.
Please see all my lace digital products: 
http://etsy.me/1wCMPHn
You will need to be able to unzip files and have software that allows you to open transparent PNG files. You will also need to know how to layer files if you wish to use the shadows. These are digital files that you can download as many times as you wish! No physical product will be sent.
They are great for graphic design, wedding invitations, bridal shower invitations, website design, blogs, scrapbooking, paper crafts and more.

Product name: 12" x 20" Glitter Heat Transfer Vinyl Sheets
Description:
12in x 20in pre-cut Glitter Heat Transfer Vinyl (HTV) Sheets. Iron-on Tshirt Vinyl available in 59 colors! Make your designs SPARKLE! For more information go to jsisigns.com.  More colors than anyone on Etsy!
MAKE YOUR DESIGNS SPARKLE.
Add the sparkle of glitter effects to any logo with JSI Glitter heat transfer film. Perfect for dance and cheer wear or anywhere you need some extra shine. Glass like fragments make this the ultimate in glitter transfer films. 90% of JSI's glitter comes from 2 different Korean suppliers.
Keep in mind, glitter often has slight shifts in adhesive and amount of glitter and slight shifts in color from batch to batch. Cutting glitter vinyl is not quite the same as cutting standard materials. Due to the thickness, we always recommend double cutting or cutting with a two pass. Also, if your plotter allows you to change the thickness of the blade, using a 60 degree blade will make the job much easier. As always, you should do a test before sending your whole job, and adjust your pressure/speed from there. If you are unfamiliar on performing a test cut, there is a guide here. We also have a guide here with some other tips on cutting glitter HTV.

100% cotton

poly/cotton blends

PVC composition
Pressure sensitive backing
Glitter rough finish
325 Microns/12.8 Mils
45/60 blade

An ideal ingredient for creams, lotions, bar soaps, lip balms. Any products where enhanced moisture retention is desired. Adds moisturizing attributes to cosmetics, toiletries and more! 
INCI : LANOLIN.
Melting point 40-48 deg. C / 104-118.4 deg. F, SAP value 80-120. Characteristics: thick, pale yellow to brownish yellow.
Lanolin is a product of sheep oil from wool. It is a water-absorbing base material and a natural emulsifier. Lanolin absorbs and holds water to the skin.
Chemically a wax instead of a fat.
(Anhydrous: Contains NO water.)

MEASURING GUIDE:
Measure your feet the way the guide bellow shows and give us these information in addition to your usual size.
Tracing Your Foot: Tape the piece of paper down to a hard floor surface.Measuring feet step .With socks on your feet (no shoes) sit with one of your feet firmly on the piece of paper that you perviously placed on the floor.
Hold the pen or pencil upright and perpendicular to the paper. Do not hold it at an angle.
Trace the line around the foot without shoes.
Make sure the pencil is resting snugly against your foot as you draw around it.
Measure the width using your measuring tape or ruler . Measure from the line on one side of your tracing, to the line on the other side.
Measure the foot from longest toe to the heel and widest part of your foot.
